<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In the PHP source, in ext/pdo/pdo_sql_parser.re, the pattern for named bound parameters is:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
    BINDCHR     = [:][a-zA-Z0-9_]+;
</code></pre>

<p>But in Zend_Db_Statement::_parseParameters(), the regular expression is:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
        /(\?|\:[a-z_]+)/
</code></pre>

<p>Please expand the regular expression in Zend_Db_Statement to be compatible with that used by PDO.</p>

    </div>
</div>

